briefdescription.para: Registers each built-in Sd field along with its C++ value type with reg.

detaileddescription.para: reg can be any type that has a member function: template <class t>=""> void RegisterField(const TfToken&);
This function will be invoked for each (field, type) pair. The template type T will be the C++ value type and the TfToken will be the field name.

briefdescription.para: Registers all possible C++ value types for built-in fields with reg.

detaileddescription.para: This is the set of C++ types that are used by built-in fields and could be returned from an SdfAbstractData container. reg can be any type that has a member function: template <class t>=""> void RegisterType();
This function will be invoked for each C++ value type, which will be given to the function as the template type T. Note that this function may be called with the same T multiple times.
